{"title": "Curious Quest", "description": "A sweet, simple tale of how friendship and honesty triumph over money. The protagonist\u2019s pun of a name\u2014Ernest Bliss\u2014foreshadows the plot in which this bored young millionaire transforms his indolent self and finds love. Typical of its era (1919), this book contains a few antisemitic stereotypes. The story was made famous by the 1936 film The Amazing Quest of Ernest Bliss with Cary Grant and Mary Brian.\r\n<br><br>\r\nE. Phillips Oppenheim (1866-1946), was born in London and wrote more than one hundred novels as well as many short stories and film adaptations, some under the name of Anthony Partridge. His 1941 autobiography, The Pool of Memory, is well worth reading. (Summary by Adrian Praetzellis)", "duration": 32895, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "460", "name": "E. Phillips Oppenheim"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/curiousquest_2111_librivox/curious_quest_2111.jpg", "copyright_year": "1919", "genres": ["Humorous Fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Adrian Praetzellis"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Adrian Praetzellis"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "J. M. Smallheer"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "mb"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Chapter 01", "readers": [1331], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/curiousquest_2111_librivox/curiousquest_01_oppenheim_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1191}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter 02", "readers": [1331], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/curiousquest_2111_librivox/curiousquest_02_oppenheim_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1095}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapters 03, 04", "readers": [1331], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/curiousquest_2111_librivox/curiousquest_03_oppenheim_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1379}, {"section": 4, "title": "Chapter 05", "readers": [1331], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/curiousquest_2111_librivox/curiousquest_04_oppenheim_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1222}, {"sect